commitResults.messageTitle: Add response to user input
commitResults.messageBody: Let's have the Duke echo the user input and close when the user enters 'bye'.

commitResults.messageTitle: Add new response for 'list'
commitResults.messageBody: When user enters 'list' into Command Line, Duke will print to screen a list of all the inputs they have entered sofar.

commitResults.messageTitle: Add ability to mark tasks as done
commitResults.messageBody:
Let's add a Task class that Duke can use, that can be marked as done.

New user response:
* 'list': displays all the tasks (with X is they are done)
* 'done (int)': marks the task at (int) as 'done'

Add Deadline.java, Event.java and Todo.java
commitResults.messageBody:
Deadline.java, Event.java and Todo.java inherit from Task.java and using Polymorphism, all the Tasks are stored in an Array List (savedInputs).

Edit Duke.java to handle the 3 different Task types.

There are a finite, small number of commands the user can enter, so using Enumerations are applicable.

Made minor changes to the Javadocs documentation in all other files.

commitResults.messageTitle: Add ability to save to Hard Disk and load from Hard Disk when Duke starts up
commitResults.messageBody:
Add 2 new methods (taskType and savedFormat) for Task.java, Todo.java, Deadline.java and Event.java

In Duke.java, when Duke starts up, it will load data from hard disk if the file already exists or create a new file. When Duke closes out ('bye'), the old file will be overwritten to
contain the contents of the new list.

JavaDoc comments added.
